They will offer, for example, a common advertisement
The new integrated newsroom of Economia in Karlín, Prague.
Economia has taken another step to transform the Centrum holding into its media house.
Since Friday, both Economia and the Centre have joint top management.
"The unification of the organizational structure and the personnel union are essential for the integration of both publishers into a common media house," comments the Vice-Chairman of the Board of Directors of Economie and the authorized CEO Kamil Čermák.
Čermák, who will lead the unified management, will be joined by the executive director of Centrum Holdings Andreas Demuth.
Pavel Vopařil was appointed as the new joint director of the business, to which the advertising director of both companies, Zuzana Tylčerová, is also subordinate.
Štěpán Burda became the new head of information technology.
The joint director of the editors is Vladimír Piskáček, whose team also includes the director of transformation Jakub Unger.
The newly established position of Director of Marketing was commissioned by Adéla Pitts.
The independent corporate communication department is newly managed by Věra Lhotská.
The joint CFO is Karel Žalud, the management of human resources for both publishers is led by Petra Slabá.
"The new organizational structure will allow us, among other things, to come to the market with a common offer of advertising products, to better connect the content creation of all published titles and, last but not least, to significantly streamline the business management of the company," Čermák added.
Economia, owned by financier Zdeněk Bakala, has entered into an agreement to buy Centrum Holdings and its Czech subsidiaries at the end of this April.
The Centrum Holdings portfolio consists of the servers Aktuálně.cz, Žena.cz, web portals, an extensive e-mail base under the brands Centrum.cz and Atlas.cz and the SMB agency Najisto or a portfolio of almost two dozen smaller websites.
Economia is the publisher of Hospodářské noviny, news server IHNED.cz, weekly magazines Respekt and Ekonom and a number of printed and internet B2B titles.
Among Czech publishers, it has long been the most successful in the sale of digital versions of its major titles.
This June, the publishing house moved to the newly built modern premises in Karlín, Prague.
