His arrival was accompanied by a chant of "the army and the people are one hand" from the mouths of hundreds of people gathered in the main lecture hall of the university.
The University of Cairo was founded in 1908 as a centre of secular education and later in the 1970s became a bastion of Islamic student movements.
Morsi took a symbolic oath in Tahrir Square on Friday, at the birthplace of the revolution that ended Mubarak's authoritarian rule last year, and solemnly promised to once again seize the presidential powers taken from his office by the military council, which took them over from the ousted leader.
