Arctic Monkeys postpone Glasgow concert due to Alex Turner's illness
Rock band Arctic Monkeys moved a concert in Glasgow after the lead singer was diagnosed with inflammation of the larynx.
The Sheffield group was due to perform Friday at the Hydro city complex.
Alex Turner's lead singer's illness, however, forced her to move the performance.
The group's announcement came after it was similarly forced to postpone Thursday's appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham.
In a statement on its official website, Arctic Monkeys said: "After the decision to postpone today's performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham and on the basis of a medical recommendation, the Arctic Monkeys Group must also postpone the performance at the Hydro complex in Glasgow planned for Friday, November 1."
"Alex Turner has been diagnosed with inflammation of the larynx and unfortunately he won't be able to get out."
The performance at the LG Arena in Birmingham will take place on November 20 and perform at the Hydro complex in Glasgow on 21 November.
All tickets for these performances remain valid.
We would like to apologize to everyone who bought the tickets for the inconvenience that this caused them.
If you need further information, please contact the customer service at the ticket office where you bought your tickets.
